'''主权国家'''（{{Lang-en|Sovereign State}}）是一个{{Link-en|政治组织|Polity|政治实体}}，由一个对某一地理区域拥有[[主权|主权]]的{{Link-en|中央集权制政府|Centralized government|中央政府}}代表。[[国际法|国际法]]将主权国家定义为拥有长住人口、确定领土、一个政府和[[國際關係學|与其他主权国家建立关系]]能力的国家。<ref>{{cite book |author1=Malcolm N. Shaw |title=International Law |date=2017-09-14 |publisher=[[剑桥大学出版社|剑桥大学出版社]] |isbn=9781316638538 |page=178 |edition=8th Edition |accessdate=2021-11-04 |language=en |quote=Article 1 of the [[蒙特維多國家權利義務公約|Montevideo Convention]] on Rights and Duties of States, 1 lays down the most widely accepted formulation of the criteria of statehood in international law. It note that the state as an international person should possess the following qualifications: '(a) a permanent population; (b) a defined territory; (c) government; and (d) capacity to enter into relations with other states'}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |editor=Nandasiri Jasentuliyana |title=Perspectives on International Law |date=1995-11-02 |publisher=Martinus Nijhoff Publishers |isbn=9789041108845 |page=20 |accessdate=2021-11-04 |language=en |quote=So far as States are concerned, the traditional definitions provided for in the Montevideo Convention remain generally accepted.}}</ref> 通常也会被理解为[[主權|主权国家即独立国家]]。<ref>{{cite book |author1=Henry Wheaton |title=Elements of International Law: With a Sketch of the History of the Science |date=1836 |publisher=B. Fellowes |page=51 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KKdJAAAAcAAJ |volume=2 |accessdate=2021-11-04 |language=en |quote=A sovereign state is generally defined to be any nation or people, whatever may be the form of its internal constitution, which governs itself independently of foreign powers. |archive-date=2022-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220107085818/https://books.google.com/books?id=KKdJAAAAcAAJ }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language |date=2006 |publisher=Houghton Mifflin Company |isbn=9780618701728 |edition=4th Edition |language=en |quote=sovereign: adj. 1. Self-governing; independent: a sovereign state.}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=The New Oxford American Dictionary |date=2005 |publisher=[[牛津大学出版社|牛津大学出版社]] |isbn=9780195170771 |edition=2ed Edition |accessdate=2021-11-04 |language=en |quote=sovereign: adjective ... [ attrib. ] (of a nation or state) fully independent and determining its own affairs.}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author1=Alain Pellet |title=The Opinions of the Badinter Arbitration Committee a Second Breath for the Self-Determination of Peoples |journal=European Journal of International Law |date=1992 |volume=3 |issue=1 |page=182 |url=http://ejil.org/pdfs/3/1/1175.pdf |accessdate=2021-11-04 |language=en |quote=The Committee considers [...] that the state is commonly defined as a community which consists of a territory and a population subject to an organized political authority; that such a state is characterized by sovereignty; [...] |archive-date=2018-10-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008101327/http://ejil.org/pdfs/3/1/1175.pdf }}</ref> 而根据国家宣示说的理论，一个主权国家可以在没有得到其他[[外交承认|主权国家承认]]的情况下存在。<ref>{{cite book |author1=Thomas D. Grant |title=The Recognition of States: Law and Practice in Debate and Evolution |date=1999 |publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group |isbn=9780275963507 |accessdate=2021-11-04 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author1=Hersch Lauterpacht |title=Recognition in International Law |date=2012 |publisher=[[剑桥大学出版社|剑桥大学出版社]] |isbn=9781107609433 |page=64 |edition=2nd Edition |accessdate=2021-11-04 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=施正鋒 |title=國家主權的取得 |url=https://www.peoplenews.tw/news/62422d0f-659a-4ed1-8420-16f7d449f2a9 |publisher=民报 |language=zh-hant |date=2016-10-11 |quote=根據「宣示說」（declaratory theory），國家的存在是客觀的事實，並不需要他人的承認；…… |access-date=2021-11-04 |archive-date=2022-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220107083414/https://www.peoplenews.tw/news/62422d0f-659a-4ed1-8420-16f7d449f2a9 }}</ref> 但是，[[有限承认国家列表|未被承认的主权国家]]会发现其难以行使完整的条约制定权或与其他主权国家建立[[外交关系|外交关系]]。

== 历史渊源 ==
自19世纪末以来，几乎整个地球已被划分为多个部分（国家），这样或多或少地为不同的国家分配了明确的边界。而在以前，相当大的土地要么无人认领，要么被遗弃，要么居住着没有组织成国家的[[游牧民族|游牧民族]]。但是即便在现代国家，也有大片偏远地区（例如[[亞馬遜雨林|亚马逊热带森林]]）要么无人居住，要么完全或主要由[[原住民|原住民]]居住（其中一些族群仍然没有经常接触）。还有一些国家并未对其整个领土拥有事实上的控制，或者这种控制存在争议。

目前，[[国际社会|国际社会]]拥有200多个主权国家，其中大部分在[[联合国|联合国]]都有代表。这些国家存在于一个国际关系体系中，每个国家通过自己的计算来考虑其他国家的政策。从这个角度看，各国都陷入了特殊的内外安全与合法化国际体系的困境。而在最近所形成的国际社会概念则指的是为执行某种关系而建立了规则、程序和机构的一组国家。因此，[[国际法|国际法]]、官方承认的主权国家的[[外交|外交]]、其组织和正式政权之间基础已经奠定。

== 现代起源 ==
{{Main|西發里亞主權體系}}

[[西發里亞主權體系|威斯特伐利亚主权体系]]是基于[[领土|领土]]的[[民族国家|民族国家]]主权概念，并且外部代理人没有在其国内结构中产生任何作用。这是一个由国家、[[跨国公司|跨国公司]]和组织所组成的国际体系，始于1648年所签订的《[[威斯特伐利亚和约|威斯特伐利亚和约]]》。

主权是一个经常被误用的术语。<ref>{{cite book |author1=Stephen D. Krasner |title=Sovereignty: Organized Hypocrisy |date=1999 |publisher=[[普林斯頓大學出版社|Princeton University Press]] |isbn=9780691007113 |accessdate=2021-11-06 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author1=Jorge Emilio Núñez |title=About the Impossibility of Absolute State Sovereignty |journal=International Journal for the Semiotics of Law - Revue internationale de Sémiotique juridique |date=2014 |volume=27 |issue=4 |pages=645–664 |doi=10.1007/s11196-013-9333-x |s2cid=150817547 |accessdate=2021-11-06 |language=en}}</ref> 直到19世纪，“文明标准”这一激进的概念还经常被用来确定世界上某些人是“未开化的”，缺乏有组织的社会。与“文明人”的“主权”相比，他们的“主权”要么完全缺乏，要么至少是劣等的，这一概念反映并构成了这种立场。<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Ralph Wilde |title=From Trusteeship to Self-Determination and Back Again: The Role of the Hague Regulations in the Evolution of International Trusteeship, and the Framework of Rights and Duties of Occupying Powers |journal=Loyola of Los Angeles International Loyola of Los Angeles International  and Comparative Law Review and Comparative Law Review |date=2009 |volume=31 |issue=1 |pages=85-142 |url=https://digitalcommons.lmu.edu/ilr/vol31/iss1/5/ |accessdate=2021-11-06 |language=en |archive-date=2021-11-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211107224413/https://digitalcommons.lmu.edu/ilr/vol31/iss1/5/ }}</ref> [[拉萨·奥本海|拉萨·奥本海姆]]说：“也许没有比主权更具争议性的概念了。这个概念从被引入政治学的那一刻起直到今天，从未有过一个这是普遍认同的意义，这是不争的事实。”

== 承认方式 ==

== 国家与政府的关系 ==
尽管“国家”与“政府”这两个术语经常互换使用，<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Edward Heath Robinson |title=The Distinction Between State and Government |journal=Geography Compass |date=2013-08 |volume=7 |issue=8 |pages=556-566 |doi=10.1111/gec3.12065 |accessdate=2021-11-06 |language=en}}</ref> 但[[国际法|国际法]]上还是将非实体国家与其政府进行了区别；事实上，“[[流亡政府|流亡政府]]”的概念就是建立在这个区别之上的。<ref name="Crawford">{{cite book |author1=James Crawford |author2=James R. Crawford |title=The Creation of States in International Law |date=2006 |publisher=[[牛津大學出版社|Oxford University Press]] |isbn=9780198260028 |edition=2nd Edition |accessdate=2021-11-06 |language=en}}</ref> 国家是非物质的法人实体，而不是任何类型的组织。<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Edward Heath Robinson |title=An ontological analysis of states: Organizations vs. legal persons |journal=Applied Ontology |date=2010 |volume=5 |issue=2 |pages=109-125 |doi=10.3233/AO-2010-0077 |accessdate=2021-11-06 |language=en}}</ref> 然而，通常情况下，只有一国政府才能对该国施加义务或约束该国，例如通过条约。<ref name="Crawford" />

== 国家灭亡 ==
一般来说，国家是持久的实体，尽管它们可以通过自愿方式或外部力量（例如军事征服）而消失。自二战结束以来，暴力废除国家政权的行为在实际上已经停止。<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Tanisha M. Fazal |title=State Death in the International System |journal=International Organization |date=2004-04 |volume=58 |issue=2 |pages=311 - 344 |doi=10.1017/S0020818304582048 |accessdate=2021-11-06 |language=en |issn=1531-5088 |s2cid=154693906}}</ref> 由于国家是非物质层面的法人实体，因而有人认为它们的灭绝不能仅由于物理力量。<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Edward Heath Robinson |title=The Involuntary Extinction of States: An Examination of the Destruction of States though the Application of Military Force by Foreign Powers since the Second World War |journal=Journal of Military Geography |date=2011 |volume=1 |pages=17-29 |url=http://www.edwardheath.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Destruction-of-States.pdf |accessdate=2021-11-06 |language=en |archive-date=2018-02-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180219023941/http://www.edwardheath.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Destruction-of-States.pdf }}</ref> 相反，军队的实际行动必须与正确的社会或司法行动相关联，才能真正地废除一个国家。

== 国家本体状态 ==
国家[[本体论_(哲学)|本体]]的状态一直是个颇有争议的主题，<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Rik Ringmar |title=On the Ontological Status of the State |journal=European Journal of International Relations |date=1996-12-01 |volume=2 |issue=4 |pages=439-466 |doi=10.1177/1354066196002004002 |s2cid=145248100 |accessdate=2021-11-07 |language=en}}</ref> 特别是国家作为一个没有人可以看到、尝到、触到或以其他方式可以检测到的客体，国家本体状态一直存疑。<ref>{{cite book |author1=Alan James |title=Sovereign Statehood: The Basis of International Society |url=https://archive.org/details/sovereignstateho0000unse |date=1986 |publisher=Allen & Unwin |isbn=9780043201909 |accessdate=2021-11-07 |language=en}}</ref>

